vaulthalla for Debian
---------------------

Install-time prompts (debconf)
==============================

The package uses debconf templates in `/debian/templates` to collect install-time
choices:

1. `vaulthalla/init-db`
2. `vaulthalla/superadmin-uid`
3. `vaulthalla/configure-nginx`

Database initialization
=======================

If `vaulthalla/init-db=true`, the maintainer script attempts to create:

- PostgreSQL role: `vaulthalla`
- PostgreSQL database: `vaulthalla`

It also writes a pending database password seed file to:

- `/run/vaulthalla/db_password`

If disabled, create the database and role manually before first runtime setup.

Super-admin UID seed
====================

The package writes a pending super-admin UID seed file to:

- `/run/vaulthalla/superadmin_uid`

This is consumed by runtime initialization on first seed pass.

Web runtime deployment
======================

The package deploys the standalone web runtime to:

- `/usr/share/vaulthalla-web`

and installs the unit:

- `/lib/systemd/system/vaulthalla-web.service`

The service is configured to run Node in production mode on localhost port
`36968`.

SQL deploy payload
==================

The package installs SQL schema/migration assets to:

- `/usr/share/vaulthalla/psql`

Core runtime initialization reads this directory on startup.

Nginx integration (conservative mode)
=====================================

When `vaulthalla/configure-nginx=true`, postinst attempts safe nginx integration
using:

- template source: `/usr/share/vaulthalla/nginx/vaulthalla.conf`
- target site: `/etc/nginx/sites-available/vaulthalla`
- enabled link: `/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/vaulthalla`

The script skips automatic nginx enablement when:

- nginx is not installed
- nginx is installed but inactive
- non-nginx listeners are detected on port 80/443
- custom nginx site layouts are already enabled

In all skip cases, install continues and logs the reason.

Remove vs purge lifecycle semantics
===================================

Remove (`apt remove` / `dpkg -r`)
---------------------------------

- stops and disables `vaulthalla-web.service`
- removes pending runtime seed files under `/run/vaulthalla`
- disables `/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/vaulthalla` only when it points to the
  package site path
- preserves:
  - `/etc/nginx/sites-available/vaulthalla`
  - `/var/lib/vaulthalla`
  - `/var/log/vaulthalla`
  - debconf answers

Purge (`apt purge` / `dpkg -P`)
-------------------------------

- includes remove behavior, plus:
  - removes package-managed nginx site file when installer created it
  - preserves nginx site file when no package-managed marker is present
  - removes `/var/lib/vaulthalla` and `/var/log/vaulthalla`
  - attempts to remove `/mnt/vaulthalla` only when empty
  - deletes `vaulthalla` system user
  - purges debconf answers

Practical clean-host validation
===============================

On a clean Debian/Ubuntu test VM:

1. Install package:
   - `sudo dpkg -i ./vaulthalla_<version>_<arch>.deb`
2. Verify services:
   - `systemctl status vaulthalla-web.service`
   - `systemctl status vaulthalla.service`
3. Verify runtime payload:
   - `test -f /usr/share/vaulthalla-web/server.js`
   - `test -d /usr/share/vaulthalla-web/.next/static`
   - `test -d /usr/share/vaulthalla/psql`
   - `test -f /usr/share/vaulthalla/psql/000_schema.sql`
4. Verify nginx decision:
   - If auto-config applied: `test -L /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/vaulthalla`
   - If skipped: check `/var/log/dpkg.log` or install output for skip reason.
5. Verify local web reachability:
   - `curl -I http://127.0.0.1:36968/`

